originContent: **An open protocol enabling communication and interoperability between opaque agentic applications.**
translatedContent: **An open protocol enabling communication and interoperability between opaque agentic applications.**

originContent: The Agent2Agent (A2A) protocol addresses a critical challenge in the AI landscape: enabling gen AI agents, built on diverse frameworks by different companies running on separate servers, to communicate and collaborate effectively - as agents, not just as tools. A2A aims to provide a common language for agents, fostering a more interconnected, powerful, and innovative AI ecosystem.
translatedContent: The Agent2Agent (A2A) protocol addresses a critical challenge in the AI landscape: enabling generative AI agents, built on diverse frameworks by different companies running on separate servers, to communicate and collaborate effectively‚Äîas agents, not just as tools. A2A aims to provide a common language for agents, fostering a more interconnected, powerful, and innovative AI ecosystem.

originContent: - Operate without exposing their internal state, memory, or tools.
translatedContent: - Operate without exposing their internal state, memory, or tools.

originContent: Join this short course on [A2A: The Agent2Agent Protocol](https://goo.gle/dlai-a2a), built in partnership with Google Cloud and IBM Research, and taught by [Holt Skinner](https://github.com/holtskinner), [Ivan Nardini](https://github.com/inardini), and [Sandi Besen](https://github.com/sandijean90).
translatedContent: Join this short course on [A2A: The Agent2Agent Protocol](https://goo.gle/dlai-a2a), built in partnership with Google Cloud and IBM Research, and taught by [Holt Skinner](https://github.com/holtskinner), [Ivan Nardini](https://github.com/inardini), and [Sandi Besen](https://github.com/sandijean90).

originContent: - **Make agents A2A-compliant:** Expose agents built with frameworks like Google ADK, LangGraph, or BeeAI as A2A servers.
translatedContent: - **Make agents A2A-compliant:** Expose agents built with frameworks like Google ADK, LangGraph, or BeeAI as A2A servers.

originContent: - **Connect agents:** Create A2A clients from scratch or using integrations to connect to A2A-compliant agents.
translatedContent: - **Connect agents:** Create A2A clients from scratch or using integrations to connect to A2A-compliant agents.

originContent: - **Orchestrate workflows:** Build sequential and hierarchical workflows of A2A-compliant agents.
translatedContent: - **Orchestrate workflows:** Build sequential and hierarchical workflows of A2A-compliant agents.

originContent: - **Multi-agent systems:** Build a healthcare multi-agent system using different frameworks and see how A2A enables collaboration.
translatedContent: - **Multi-agent systems:** Build a healthcare multi-agent system using different frameworks and see how A2A enables collaboration.

originContent: - **A2A and MCP:** Learn how A2A complements MCP by enabling agents to collaborate with each other.
translatedContent: - **A2A and MCP:** Learn how A2A complements MCP by enabling agents to collaborate with each other.

originContent: As AI agents become more prevalent, their ability to interoperate is crucial for building complex, multi-functional applications. A2A aims to:
translatedContent: As AI agents become more prevalent, their ability to interoperate is crucial for building complex, multi-functional applications. A2A aims to:

originContent: - **Break Down Silos:** Connect agents across different ecosystems.
translatedContent: - **Break Down Silos:** Connect agents across different ecosystems.

originContent: - **Enable Complex Collaboration:** Allow specialized agents to work together on tasks that a single agent cannot handle alone.
translatedContent: - **Enable Complex Collaboration:** Allow specialized agents to work together on tasks that a single agent cannot handle alone.

originContent: - **Promote Open Standards:** Foster a community-driven approach to agent communication, encouraging innovation and broad adoption.
translatedContent: - **Promote Open Standards:** Foster a community-driven approach to agent communication, encouraging innovation and broad adoption.

originContent: - **Preserve Opacity:** Allow agents to collaborate without needing to share internal memory, proprietary logic, or specific tool implementations, enhancing security and protecting intellectual property.
translatedContent: - **Preserve Opacity:** Allow agents to collaborate without needing to share internal memory, proprietary logic, or specific tool implementations, enhancing security and protecting intellectual property.

originContent: - **Agent Discovery:** Via "Agent Cards" detailing capabilities and connection info.
translatedContent: - **Agent Discovery:** Via "Agent Cards" detailing capabilities and connection info.

originContent: - **Flexible Interaction:** Supports synchronous request/response, streaming (SSE), and asynchronous push notifications.
translatedContent: - **Flexible Interaction:** Supports synchronous request/response, streaming (SSE), and asynchronous push notifications.

originContent: - **Rich Data Exchange:** Handles text, files, and structured JSON data.
translatedContent: - **Rich Data Exchange:** Handles text, files, and structured JSON data.

originContent: - **Enterprise-Ready:** Designed with security, authentication, and observability in mind.
translatedContent: - **Enterprise-Ready:** Designed with security, authentication, and observability in mind.

originContent: - Formalize inclusion of authorization schemes and optional credentials directly within the `AgentCard`.
translatedContent: - Formalize inclusion of authorization schemes and optional credentials directly within the `AgentCard`.
